abstract: >-
  PathoMAN 2.0 is a hybrid retrieval-augmented agentic pipeline for ACMG/AMP
  germline variant classification. It implements a 10-node LangGraph state
  machine integrating ClinVar, gnomAD v4 + v3 + v2, Ensembl VEP, dbNSFP,
  ClinGen Dosage Sensitivity, and a FAISS-indexed corpus of six SVI/VCEP
  source documents. All six active ClinGen Sequence Variant Interpretation
  Working Group overrides are applied by default (Abou Tayoun 2018 PVS1
  decision tree, Riggs 2020 Haploinsufficiency Score gate, Ghosh 2018 PM2
  strength downgrade, Pejaver 2022 PP3/BP4 calibration, Tavtigian 2018
  Bayesian combining, SVI 2018 PP5/BP6 deprecation). Combining is
  dual-framework (Tavtigian primary + Richards 2015 Table 5 in parallel)
  with automated disagreement detection. A three-layer Microsoft Responsible
  AI guardrail architecture wraps every classification with deterministic
  rule subsumption, structured-output schema validation, and citation
  enforcement. Built for educational and research use only.
